         <abstract>
            <p>Directional Newton methods for functions f of n variables are shown to converge, under standard assumptions, to a solution of f(x) = 0. The rate of convergence is quadratic, for near-gradient directions, and directions along components of the gradient of f with maximal modulus. These methods are applied to solving systems of equations without inversion of the Jacobian matrix.</p>
